schemeDefinitions.definitions_md:
An Industrial Park refers to an estate developed on a minimum area of 20 hectares for establishing at least 10 industrial units, with an additional 2 units required for every 5 hectares or part thereof. These parks are meant for manufacturing products or services and must include basic infrastructure such as developed plots, internal roads, water distribution, sewage, power distribution, communication facilities, worker hostels, and other necessary amenities.
&lt;br&gt;

In Vanbandhu talukas, the minimum area requirement is 5 hectares for at least 5 industrial units, with 1 additional unit required for every additional hectare. Industrial Parks spanning over 100 hectares will receive government support for peripheral external link infrastructure like roads, water supply, power substations, gas, and effluent disposal.
&lt;br&gt;

Industrial Parks established on land allotted by GIDC or in closed textile mills/industrial units are also eligible under this scheme. Institutions purchasing land for Industrial Parks will be deemed bona fide industrial land users and can obtain permissions under the Gujarat Tenancy and Agricultural Lands Laws (Amendment) Act, 1997. Such parks can allot plots/sheds to industrial projects.
